## v2.0.0 (2026-06-30)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1441 "Merge 4 Claude agent modules" — first
real, verified-local execution of the shim discipline (in the MERGE direction).
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

- Promoted the skill from `unverified` to `verified-local` and added a
  `verification: verified-local` frontmatter field plus a `history` field.
- Added the **Shim Consolidation (Merge Direction)** section to `## Verified Workflow`:
  the inverse of the split — consolidate 3-4 always-co-imported modules into one
  canonical module (`agent_config.py`) while keeping the originals as explicit
  re-export shims. Includes Steps C1-C4.
- **Corrected the central re-export-shim recommendation:** v1.0.0's Explicit shim
  templates carried `# ruff: noqa: F401`. That is WRONG for an explicit `name as name`
  alias — the alias IS ruff's recognized re-export idiom, so F401 never fires and the
  unused directive trips RUF100. Removed `# ruff: noqa: F401` from Option B and from the
  "Explicit Variant" template, with an explicit warning. (Wildcard `import *` shim still
  needs F403/F401.)
- Added four real **Failed Attempts** rows (replacing the N/A placeholder): the noqa/RUF100
  trap, RUF022 `__all__` isort-sort requirement, private-symbol/reload/caplog-logger test
  repointing, and the need for a full-surface parity test.
- Added a **Merge-Direction Parameters** table (#1441) under Results & Parameters.
- Added three "When to Use" triggers and a 7th `description` clause for the merge direction.
- Added a `## Verified On` row for #1441 and a #1441 reference.
- New tags: `re-export`, `ruff-f401`, `module-consolidation`.

### Why

v1.0.0 was a pure plan for the 52-file SPLIT (issue #1177) and was never executed, so its
shim templates were never run through ruff. Executing the inverse (MERGE) refactor for #1441
exercised the same shim discipline for real and exposed concrete, durable lints the plan got
wrong — most importantly that an explicit-`as`-alias re-export shim must NOT carry
`# ruff: noqa: F401` (RUF100 fails CI otherwise). It also surfaced RUF022 `__all__` ordering,
the private-symbol/caplog-logger test-repointing trap, and the value of a full-surface
shim-parity test. These are exactly the steps a future merge/split would otherwise re-discover.

